## 🚀 Quick Start Guide (For Windows Users)
Want to use Direct-Drop without looking at any code? Follow these simple steps to set up the ultimate right-click file transfer tool on your Windows machine.

### 📥 1. Download
1. Go to the [Releases page](https://github.com/AnisurRahman-46/Direct-Drop/releases/tag/v1.0.0) of this repository.
2. Download the latest `directdrop.exe` file.
3. Move this file into a safe, permanent folder on your laptop (e.g., `Documents/DirectDrop_App/`). *Do not leave it in your Downloads folder.*

### ⚙️ 2. One-Time Setup (The Right-Click Hack)
We are going to add Direct-Drop to your Windows "Send To" menu so you can instantly share files without opening any apps.

1. Press `Windows Key + R` on your keyboard to open the Run box.
2. Type `shell:sendto` and press Enter. A hidden folder will open.
3. Open another window and find where you saved `directdrop.exe`.
4. **Hold down the `Alt` key**, then click and drag `directdrop.exe` into that hidden `SendTo` folder. This creates a shortcut.
5. Rename the new shortcut to something cool, like `🚀 Direct-Drop`.

### 📱 3. How to Use It
1. Right-click on any file (or multiple files) you want to send to your phone.
2. Hover over **Send to** -> click **Direct-Drop**.
3. A black terminal window will pop up generating a secure QR code.
4. Scan the QR code with your phone's camera.
5. Tap "Get" on your phone's screen to instantly download the file over your local Wi-Fi!

*(To stop sharing, just press CTRL+C).*

### ⚠️ Important Windows Security Note
Because Direct-Drop is a brand new, custom-built application, **Windows Defender SmartScreen** might flag it and say "Windows protected your PC" the first time you run it. 
* This is completely normal for independent software. 
* Simply click **"More info"** and then **"Run anyway"**. 

